76492851520052/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:42:{i:0;s:142:"If any of these electronic components are faulty the garage door opener will not function properly and may not allow the garage door to close.";i:1;s:248:"Assuming that you have checked the safety sensors for the issues listed above and you determine that the problem is with the garage door opener it is recommended to contact a professional IDEA certified garage door technician to make the necessary.";i:2;s:136:"If the beam is broken or the sensors are misaligned the sensor lights will go off and subsequently tell the operator not close the door.";i:3;s:127:"The garage door may attempt to go down but will come right back up and the overhead light on the garage door opener will blink.";i:4;s:51:"This also disables any remotes or wireless keypads.";i:5;s:140:"If your garage door opener wont close and the motor unit lights blink 10 times it usually means you have a problem with your safety sensors.";i:6;s:143:"In this video from Sears PartsDirect well show you some simple fixes like checking the garage door openers alignment and clearing obstructions.";i:7;s:94:"The most common cause for your door not closing in the morning but will close at night is the.";i:8;s:68:"These sensors prevent the door from closing if the sensor beam gets.";i:9;s:83:"This safety feature is required on garage doors and keeps the door from closing on.";i:10;s:56:"If its not working troubleshoot your garage door opener.";i:11;s:303:"Hub and Sensor Are Out of Sync If you are experiencing Close Errors or unexpected behavior in the myQ app after two or more attempts it is recommended that you operate the garage door opener locally from the control panel on the wall or a handheld remote control and fully open and close the door twice.";i:12;s:106:"If the garage door sensors are detecting any objects or debris your garage door will not close completely.";i:13;s:66:"Inspect your garage entrance and floor for any potential culprits.";i:14;s:112:"If you determine that the sensors are not blocked you could be dealing with faulty or misaligned safety sensors.";i:15;s:72:"There is nothing more frustrating than when your garage door wont close.";i:16;s:147:"If you have to press and hold the inside wall button to close the garage door your safety sensors are either misaligned or may need to be replaced.";i:17;s:96:"If your garage door wont close after aligning the safety sensors you might need to replace them.";i:18;s:67:"Garage door opener safety sensors can go bad due to age excess sun.";i:19;s:77:"However the garage door opener will not move the garage door without sensors.";i:20;s:64:"To operate the door you will have to open and close it manually.";i:21;s:88:"Each garage door should have a manual release that will allow you to raise and lower it.";i:22;s:106:"Activate the emergency release by pulling the cord attached to the trolley on the garage door opener rail.";i:23;s:88:"My garage door opener wont close when the timerlight is still on after the door is open.";i:24;s:77:"Issue is not the lightbulb since the problem exists when using no lightbulbs.";i:25;s:158:"Ive installed Liftmaster 365LM receiver to Liftmaster 2000SDR as an alternative since my other newer garage door opener is 315Mhz and have the 315Mhz remotes.";i:26;s:59:"Detach the opener by pulling the emergency handle downward.";i:27;s:62:"The next step is to attempt to open your garage door manually.";i:28;s:79:"This will determine if the issue is connected to the door itself or the opener.";i:29;s:71:"If you are able to raise your garage door easily it is not the problem.";i:30;s:69:"This indicates that something in the opener system has malfunctioned.";i:31;s:117:"If your garage door opens ok but wont close then its possible the safety reversing sensors are not correctly aligned.";i:32;s:67:"Dont just assume that if the path is clear that the sensors are ok.";i:33;s:42:"This problem bugged me for several months.";i:34;s:52:"Check the connected unit close the electric circuit.";i:35;s:84:"The OPEN force limit has been activated - the door has come to a halt while opening.";i:36;s:78:"If the door has come to a halt for no obvious reason check the door mechanics.";i:37;s:48:"My garage door will start to close then reverse.";i:38;s:41:"Then the opener light flashes on and off.";i:39;s:117:"Everything Ive read says this is because the safety sensors are misaligned blinded by direct sunlight or bad somehow.";i:40;s:52:"Well Ive checked the sensors and heres what I found.";i:41;s:73:"When the door is closed and the garage is dim or dark I can see that the.";}}